Features

Role-based user experience (Student, Distributor, Volunteer, Restaurant)

Browse restaurants offering available meals

View detailed meal information

See food tags and allergens

Track meal quantities

Map view for logistics coordination

Restaurant donation submission

Modern mobile UI built with React Native

Technologies Used

The project was built using the following technologies:

React Native

Expo

Expo Router

TypeScript

React Query

Lucide React Native Icons

Node.js

npm

These technologies allow the application to run across multiple mobile platforms while maintaining clean project structure and maintainable code.

System Requirements

Before running the project, make sure the following are installed on your system:

Node.js (version 18 or higher recommended)

npm (installed with Node.js)

VS Code or another code editor

Expo CLI (installed automatically through npx)

You can verify Node installation by running:

node -v
npm -v
Installation

Follow these steps to set up the project locally.

1. Clone or Download the Project

Download the project folder and navigate to it using the terminal.

Example:

cd Desktop/mealmatch
2. Install Project Dependencies

Run the following command to install all required packages:

npm install --legacy-peer-deps

This installs all dependencies listed in the package.json file.

3. Start the Development Server

Run the following command:

npx expo start

This will start the Expo development server.

Once started, you will see:

a QR code

development options

browser preview

Running the Application

After running npx expo start, you can launch the app in several ways:

Web Browser

Press

w

in the terminal to open the web version.

Mobile Device

Install Expo Go on your phone and scan the QR code shown in the terminal.

Android Emulator

Press

a

if an Android emulator is installed.

